The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for traffic prediction in transportation networks, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory (LSTM) neural networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the proposed method and its application to traffic prediction. The other categories are also possible, as they are relevant to the use of deep learning and neural networks in general.
